Placement1: Direct job offers/active offer of vacancies by PES staff
Placement2: Placement staff uses computer-based data bank with the registered job vacancies
Placement3: Placement staff uses computer-based data bank of the registered jobseekers
Placement4: Self service access to job offers displayed in local offices or sub units
Placement5: Self-service facilities: Internet based PES vacancies bank
Placement6: Internet based PES vacancies and registered users bank;  users may themselves process and change their  profile
Profiling1: Systematic assessment of chances to labour market integration (profiling)
Profiling2: If profiling is applied: profiling based only on counsellor/ placement officer’s assessment
Profiling3: If profiling is applied: only statistical profiling based on formal models and technical (IT) devices
Profiling4: If profiling is applied: Mixed type of profiling based on placement officer’s assessment supported by technical devices
JSearch1: Personal job search interviews and/or assistance: information for searching and finding vacancies in PES local offices/ local agencies
JSearch3: Internet information on job search ( practical advices : cv writing , cover letter, presentation etc.)
JSearch4: Individual action plans/ reintegration agreements that define job search activities and targets
JSearch6: Referral to externally provided applicants training
JSearch7: Referral to specialised placement agencies/ providers for personalized, special services
Access1: Access to applicants data bank (incl. contact information) at PES offices
Access2: Employer has to contact the responsible PES officer to refer to the applicant
Access3: Internet access to applicants/CV data bank with applicants’ contact information
Access4: Employer can contact the applicant directly ( anymous info)
Recruit1: Personal support services for recruitment  (eye-to-eye) contact at PES office or employer’s site
Recruit2: Personal support services for recruitment  by telephone -through placement officer
Recruit3: Personal support services for recruitment by telephone -callcenter
Recruit4: Personal support services for recruitment by email/online
Special1: (Pre-)selection of suitable candidates and proposal to employer by the PES staff
Special3: Group information for suitable workers commissioned by employer
Special4: Targeted site visits in selected companies/ branches to raise demand and to develop specific service packages
Special6: Customer segmentation: different service levels/depths for different customer groups
Special7: Personal PES advice/ support in case of company crisis (e.g. employment maintenance but also organisation of lay-offs etc.)
Information1: Labour market statistics at national level
Information2: Labour market statistics at regional level/units
Information3: Labour market statistics at local level/units
Information4: Labour market statistics  for the government and/or statistical institutions
Information5: Labour market information to the general through paper leaflets/ brochures
Information6: Labour market information to the general through Internet website
Information7: Labour market information to the general through Internet download options
Information8: Labour market research (beyond monitoring of labour market development)
Information9: PES is a member of an employment observatory
Policies1: General vocational guidance (i.e. counseling/ advice) for young people (school-to-work transition) and adults
Policies2: PES/organisation itself is active as provider of vocational training measures (focus qualications/ competencies)
Policies3: Funding and/or referral of vocational training sessions provided by external training organisations
Policies4: Work testing/ placement into temporary work trial
Policies6: Wage cost subsidies to promote recruitment of unemployed persons
Policies7: Job creation measures as additional (public) employment in restricted target areas
Policies8: Employment maintenance measures (short time work schemes etc) for workers running the risk of ecomic layoff
Policies9: Programmes to promote the mobility of workers
Targets1: Promotion of labour market integration of young people (age < 25)
UB1: Management of unemployment benefits (as a rule based on entitlements)
UB2: Management of jobseekers allowances / basic income support for jobseekers (as a rule means-tested)
UB3: Management of social assistance allowances or related additional allowances
Migration2: Information and advice for finding jobs abroad
Migration3: Assistance to foreign employers looking for migrant workers
Migration4: Assistance to foreign workers already residing in the country
